On Mekotronics R58S2, detect the recovery/download key and enter RockUSB.

Two fixes on top of the generic Rockchip download-key path:

1. RK3588 DT names the converter "adc@fec10000" (label saradc). Generic
   rockchip_dnl_key_pressed() only matches names starting with "saradc", so it
   never finds the device and the recovery button appears dead. Also accept
   "adc@" names.

2. Kernel Blueberry DT uses press-threshold-microvolt = <17000> on SARADC
   channel 1 (KEY_VOLUMEUP / recovery). RK3588 SARADC is 12-bit with a 1.8 V
   reference, so 17 mV ~= raw count 39. Raise KEY_DOWN_MAX_VAL from 30 to 50.

When the key is pressed, start RockUSB on eMMC; if that returns, fall back to
the existing reset-to-BROM behavior. Board-scoped (board_mekotronics-r58s2).

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
--- a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
 
 #include <adc.h>
 #include <command.h>
+#include <cli.h>
 #include <env.h>
 #include <log.h>
 #include <asm/io.h>
@@ -36,7 +37,7 @@ void set_back_to_bootrom_dnl_flag(void)
  * some special boards.
  */
 #define KEY_DOWN_MIN_VAL	0
-#define KEY_DOWN_MAX_VAL	30
+#define KEY_DOWN_MAX_VAL	50
 
 __weak int rockchip_dnl_key_pressed(void)
 {
@@ -52,7 +53,8 @@ __weak int rockchip_dnl_key_pressed(void)
 
 	ret = -ENODEV;
 	uclass_foreach_dev(dev, uc) {
-		if (!strncmp(dev->name, "saradc", 6)) {
+		if (!strncmp(dev->name, "saradc", 6) ||
+		    !strncmp(dev->name, "adc@", 4)) {
 			ret = adc_channel_single_shot(dev->name, 1, &val);
 			break;
 		}
@@ -75,6 +77,10 @@ void rockchip_dnl_mode_check(void)
 {
 	if (rockchip_dnl_key_pressed()) {
 		printf("download key pressed, entering download mode...");
+		printf("\nentering rockusb mode on mmc0...\n");
+		cli_simple_run_command("rockusb 0 mmc 0", 0);
+
+		printf("rockusb exited, falling back to bootrom download mode...");
 		set_back_to_bootrom_dnl_flag();
 		do_reset(NULL, 0, 0, NULL);
 	}
